PacificHome feed in XML, JSONL and CSV formats. Also includes a .txt file containing all the attributes
in the feed

Notes:
    1. The XML file was originally translated from WorldMarket's source feed (November 2019)
       This translated feed is used as source for other conversions (jsonl, csv)
       We don't do any more WorldMarket -> PacificHome translations

        1.1 New full_feed xml file generated using using Python instead of Java. 
            Script dir: ~/work/brxdemos_tmp/projects/demoEngineering/translators/demo-engineering-translators/src/main/resources/brxdemos/pacifichome/translate/feed/scripts

    2. File naming conventions (jsonl example):
        filename: full_feed_preprocessed_03312021_09072022.jsonl
                - "03312021" is the date of xml-feed file that was translated to jsonl
                - "09072022" latest update to the jsonl content (eg, add "brand = Pacific Good")

    3. JSONL format is used to ingest + index feed in Discovery dataConnect
    4. CSV format is used in Engagement
        - We have not indexed this in Discovery side. Therefore it is not 'verified' by Discovery/Connect code
    5. The attributes.txt file has list of attributes in the feed

